CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 18, 1950, pg. 4 reads: "Don't Believe In Signs - Although the signs state that there is to be no parking on the east side of Herron Avenue, between Wylie Avenue and Bryn Mawr Road, "at any time." that side of the street can be found full of parked automobiles "at any time." Photo above was taken at 5 o'clock Tuesday afternoon, Feb. 14. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Intersection of Wylie Avenue and Herron Avenue with Silverman Rexall Drug store and [...]bell shop
